- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with interference channels and beamforming, which are topics related to information theory.
- cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper uses game theoretic models and solution concepts to analyze the conflict between the links.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper deals with interference channels, which are a type of wireless network.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a coordination process for the distributed implementation of the beamforming problem.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as beamforming is a technique used in audio and video signal processing.
